  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-chorizo-and-cherry-tomato-risotto/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-chorizo-and-cherry-tomato-risotto/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half</strong> the<strong> sliced spring onion</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and cook for 1 min or until beginning to soften slightly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-chorizo-and-cherry-tomato-risotto/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>diced chorizo</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to brown</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped thyme</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pan and mix well</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-chorizo-and-cherry-tomato-risotto/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>arborio rice</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-chorizo-and-cherry-tomato-risotto/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes</strong> when the rice is nearly cooked – this is your <strong>chorizo & cherry tomato</strong> <strong>risotto</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-chorizo-and-cherry-tomato-risotto/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>risotto</strong> from the heat then add your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and stir through</p><p>Taste for seasoning adding more<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and add to a bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/simple-chorizo-and-cherry-tomato-risotto/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chorizo & cherry tomato</strong> <strong>risotto</strong> in a bowl with the <strong>salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
